  "conditionals": 70,
  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "The yeast mating response is a classic MAPK cascade triggered by pheromones. \u03b1-factor (from MAT\u03b1 cells) or a-factor (from MATa cells) bind GPCRs (Ste2/Ste3), activating G\u03b1 (Gpa1) dissociation from G\u03b2\u03b3 (Ste4/Ste18). Free G\u03b2\u03b3 recruits scaffold Ste5, which assembles the MAPK cascade: Ste11 (MAPKKK), Ste7 (MAPKK), Fus3/Kss1 (MAPK). Activated Fus3 phosphorylates transcription factor Ste12, relieves Far1-mediated repression, induces mating genes, and causes G1 arrest for shmoo formation.",
  "id": "yeast_mapk_mating",
  "keywords": [
    "MAPK",
    "pheromone response",
    "Fus3",
    "Ste12",
    "mating",
    "shmoo"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
